text: October unemployment rates ranged from 1.7% in MD to 5.4% in NV.
Only Hawaii and DC saw house prices fall between Q3 2022 and Q3 2023.
Real state GDP in Q1 2023 was higher than in Q1 2022 in all states except CT and IN.
October average private weekly earnings in states ranged from $891 in MS to $1,409 in WA.
Real manufacturing GDP growth Q1 2022 and Q1 2023 ranged from -6.8% in AK to 2.1% in NV and TX.
Retail jobs in October 2023 were at or above 2019 levels for 28 states.
The unemployment rate increased in 39 states from September to October.
MN and 31 other states have seen continuous growth in house prices since Q1 2013.
Leisure and hospitality jobs in Oct 2023 were at or above Oct 2022 levels in all but four states.
Four states saw lower real retail GDP levels in Q1 2023 than Q1 2005: CT, NH, RI, and WV.
